page.title: 02 THE SEA
page.content: At the beach there are cockles and samphire.Samphire is a seaweed that is boiled and pickled and then eaten.Kids are found on the beach,they are made of brushwood and buried in the sand to form a barrier to stop sand being blown away,they also help to preserve the sea bank.Many locals go to the beach to find cockles and pick samphire.Ships can be seen from the beach going to {Grimsby Docks }or { {Immingham Docks },but some tankers unload at a monobuoy and the oil pumped into storage tanks at {Tetney } .It is pumped underground to the oil refinerys at {Killingholme }.
